Author: Dylan Conlin <dylan.conlin@gmail.com>
Date:   Sat Feb 7 12:14:39 2026 -0800

    fix: add instance eviction (LRU/TTL) + SSE cleanup to prevent 8.4GB memory growth

    Root cause: Instance cache grows unboundedly by directory key. Each unique
    x-opencode-directory creates permanent Instance with bootstrapped services.
    Multi-agent orch-go usage causes 8.4GB RSS → macOS jetsam kill.

    Fixes:
    - LRU eviction on Instance cache (max 20 live, 30min TTL for idle)
    - SSE /event route cleanup: shared teardown for both abort and close paths
      (was: connected=40/disconnected=0 on server-initiated close)
    - Instance create/evict/dispose counters for observability

    Evidence: investigation at orch-go/.kb/investigations/2026-02-07-inv-opencode-server-memory-leak-4gb.md

